<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="S" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Sly2" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Sly,</orth> adj. 1) artful, cunning, insidious: <bibl n="shak. luc 1399" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 1399</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tgv 2.6.41" default="NO" valid="yes">Gent. II, 6, 41</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jn 2.567" default="NO" valid="yes">John II, 567</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 3.3.160" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C III, 3, 160</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 1.3.53" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 I, 3, 53</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 4.4.171" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 4, 171</bibl> (Ff <emph>s. and bloody,</emph> Qq <emph>bloody, treacherous</emph>). <bibl n="shak. h8 1.3.39" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 I, 3, 39</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 4.4.59" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. IV, 4, 59</bibl> (cf. <emph>crafty</emph>). <bibl n="shak. cym 1.5.75" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. I, 5, 75</bibl>.<lb />2) secret, imperceptible: <cit><quote>the s. slow hours shall not determinate the dateless limit of thy dear exile,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r2 1.3.150" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 I, 3, 150</bibl></cit> (F<hi rend="sub">2</hi> and some M. Edd. <emph>fly-slow</emph>).
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>